Class Implementor

java.lang.Object
info.kgeorgiy.ja.dmitriev.implementor.BaseImplementor
info.kgeorgiy.ja.dmitriev.implementor.Implementor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Impler, JarImpler
public class Implementor extends BaseImplementor implements JarImpler
The class allows you to generate valid code using the token class and packing in jar. Class implementing JarImpler. The class also contains a console interface. And also extends BaseImplementor.

21

    • implImplementJar

      private static void implImplementJar(Class<?> token, Path jarFile) throws ImplerException

      Parameters:
      token - Class that will be implementation
      jarFile - Path that will be generated
      Throws:
      ImplerException - couldn't implement
      ImplerException - couldn't write, i.e. the IOException occurred
      ImplerException - couldn't found java compiler

    • implementJar

      public void implementJar(Class<?> token, Path jarFile) throws ImplerException
      Description copied from interface: JarImpler
      Produces .jar file implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

      Generated class' name should be the same as the class name of the type token with Impl suffix added.

      Specified by:
      implementJar in interface JarImpler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      jarFile - target .jar file.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      This function is a console interface of implementJar(Class, Path).

      Required argument is classname. Usage: "<class-name> or -jar <class-name> <file.java>". If it's first format, then will be call BaseImplementor.main(String[]) All arguments must be non-null. If errors and warnings occur, they will be write in STDERR Errors inherited from BaseImplementor.implement(Class, Path).
